"question":"Compare and explain the purpose of the following mathematical functions: AVERAGE, INT, ROUND, MOD, and SQRT.",
"answer":"These functions perform specific mathematical operations in Excel:\n1. AVERAGE(range): Calculates and returns the mathematical mean of all given numbers within a selected cell range.\n2. INT(number): Rounds a decimal number completely down to the nearest integer value.\n3. ROUND(number, num_digit): Rounds a number precisely to a specified number of decimal digits.\n4. MOD(number, divisor): Calculates division but only returns the remainder left after the number is divided by the divisor.\n5. SQRT(number): Returns the mathematical square root of a specific given number.",
